MERN Backend API with AWS ECS Deployment

This is a MERN backend project built with TypeScript, Express, and MongoDB. The project is configured to deploy on AWS ECS using Fargate and Docker with CI/CD via GitHub Actions.

Features

RESTful API endpoints for items

MongoDB integration

Dockerized backend

CI/CD pipeline using GitHub Actions

Deployment to AWS ECS with Fargate

Prerequisites

Node.js v18+

npm

Docker

AWS account with ECS, ECR, and IAM configured

GitHub repository

Getting Started
1. Clone Repository
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/<repository-name>.git
cd <repository-name>

2. Install Dependencies
npm install

3. Configure Environment

Create a .env file in the root:

PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=<your-mongodb-connection-string>

4. Run Locally
npm run build
npm run start


API should run at: http://localhost:5000/

GitHub Push Instructions

Initialize Git (if not already):

git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"


Add remote repository:

git remote add origin https://github.com/<your-username>/<repository-name>.git


Push to GitHub:

git branch -M main
git push -u origin main

Docker & AWS Deployment Overview

Dockerize your backend:

docker build -t backend .
docker run -p 5000:5000 backend


AWS ECS Deployment:

Push Docker image to AWS ECR

Create ECS Task Definition with Fargate

Create ECS Cluster and Service

Configure Security Group to allow inbound traffic to port 5000

Use GitHub Actions for CI/CD to automate build and deploy

Secrets needed in GitHub Actions:

AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID

AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY

AWS_REGION

ECR_REPOSITORY_URI

ECS_CLUSTER

ECS_SERVICE